    bf:responsibilityStatement "a Carolo Hoolo ... = 1. Cato's distichs concerning manners ; 2. Excellent sayings of the seven wise men of Greece ; 3. Publius's stage verses, of Seneca's proverbs in Latin and English ; likewise Cato construed grammatically, with one row Latin, and another English : whereby little children may understandingly learn the rules of common behaviour / by Charles Hoole ..." ;
